A four-member parliamentary committee on Transport, Public Works and Housing on Thursday toured Busia county following a petition from 166 residents about congestion by trailers at the Busia and Malaba borders.Navakholo MP Emmanuel Wangwe led the team that included Luanda MP Chris Mulele, Aduma Owuor (Nyakach) and petitioner and Matayos MP Geoffrey Odanga.Odanga said residents complain about the truck pileup, saying they were sitting on a time bomb .Residents say the pileup has hurt trade.